headline: Will Target’s (TGT) Accessible Self-Checkout Strategy Reshape Its Competitive Edge?
summary: Earlier this week, Target announced the nationwide rollout of a first-of-its-kind accessible self-checkout experience designed for guests with disabilities, including those who are blind or have low vision. This innovation not only enhances convenience for millions of shoppers but also reflects a renewed emphasis on inclusive design in Target’s in-store technology strategy. We’ll explore how this push for accessible retail technology could influence Target’s long-term competitive position...
